# UI Components

Always use **shadcn/ui** components for all UI elements. Never build raw HTML replacements when a shadcn primitive exists.

## Available primitives (non-exhaustive)

`Button`, `Input`, `Badge`, `Dialog`, `Sheet`, `Checkbox`, `Select`, `Separator`, `ScrollArea`, `Tooltip`, `Popover`, `DropdownMenu`, `Tabs`, `Card`, `Avatar`, `Skeleton`, `Switch`, `Label`, `Textarea`

## Rules

- **Buttons** → `<Button variant="..." size="...">` — never `<button>` raw
- **Text inputs / search** → `<Input>` — never `<input>` raw
- **Slide-out drawers / sidebars** → `<Sheet>` with `<SheetContent side="left|right">`
- **Checkboxes** → `<Checkbox>` — never custom-drawn boxes
- **Modals** → `<Dialog>` — never custom overlay divs
- **Badges / counts** → `<Badge>`
- **Tooltips** → `<Tooltip>` / `<TooltipProvider>`

## Adding new shadcn components

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — raw elements
<button onClick={fn}>Save</button>
<input placeholder="Search..." />

// ✅ GOOD — shadcn primitives
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";

<Button onClick={fn}>Save</Button>
<Input placeholder="Search..." />
```
